On July 3, 2018, President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation expressing condolences for the shooting at the Capital Gazette newspaper in Annapolis, Maryland. The proclamation calls upon God to be with the victims and their families, and orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at various locations, including the White House, public buildings, military posts, and naval vessels, until sunset on July 3, 2018. The proclamation also directs that the flag be flown at half-staff at United States embassies, consular offices, and other facilities abroad for the same period of time.